    <owl:Ontology rdf:about="https://tomascp-sudo.github.io/medical-device-ontology/ontology.owl">
        <owl:versionIRI rdf:resource="https://tomascp-sudo.github.io/medical-device-ontology/ontology.owl/version1"/>
        <dc:description xml:lang="en">This ontology models relationships between devices, manufacturers, risks, incidents and field safety corrective actions (FSCA), enabling integrated regulatory surveillance within a single semantic framework.</dc:description>
        <dc:description>This ontology provides a semantic representation of the medical devices domain, with a focus on device classification, safety, incidents, and corrective actions.
It is built using OWL (Web Ontology Language) to ensure logical consistency and interoperability, and it incorporates SWRL rules to support inference and reasoning.

Core Concepts

MedicalDevice:
Represents the general concept of a medical device. It is the superclass for more specific types such as ImplantableDevice or ActiveImplant.
Each device can be described through properties such as name, manufacturer, classification, and device type.

ImplantableDevice / ActiveImplant:
These classes represent specific categories of medical devices, especially those that are placed inside the human body or require an energy source to function.
They are relevant for determining risk level and regulatory classification.

RiskClass:
Represents the regulatory classification of the device, such as Class I, Class IIa, Class IIb, or Class III.
These classes are used to organize devices according to their level of risk and control requirements.

CorrectiveAction:
Represents actions taken in response to incidents, defects, or safety issues related to a medical device.
These actions help model post-market surveillance and device safety procedures.

Properties

Object Properties:
Define relationships between instances of different classes. Examples include:

hasClassification – connects a medical device to its regulatory class
hasCorrectiveAction – connects a device or incident to a corrective action
manufacturedBy – connects a medical device to its manufacturer

Data Properties:
Define literal attributes. Examples include:

hasName – assigns a name to a medical device
hasModel – represents the commercial or technical model of the device
hasSerialNumber – identifies a specific device instance
hasRiskLevel – expresses the level of risk associated with a device

Individuals
The ontology contains a set of individuals representing example devices, classifications, manufacturers, and corrective actions.
These individuals allow reasoning engines to infer new facts and validate the consistency of the ontology.

Rules and Inference
Using SWRL rules, the ontology supports rule-based reasoning to infer classifications, detect relations between device types and risk classes, and support safety analysis.
Inside Protégé, the reasoner used was Pellet.

Extensibility
The ontology is designed to be extensible and adaptable.
New classes, properties, and individuals can be incorporated as the domain evolves.</dc:description>
        <dc:title>Medical Devices Classification and Safety Ontology</dc:title>
        <dc:title xml:lang="en">Ontology for High-Risk Medical Devices and IVDs</dc:title>
        <terms1:abstract>This ontology provides a semantic model for high-risk medical devices and in vitro diagnostic devices, including their manufacturers, risk classes, incidents, and field safety corrective actions. It supports formal knowledge representation, reasoning, and interoperability in regulatory surveillance scenarios under MDR and IVDR frameworks.</terms1:abstract>
        <terms1:created rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#date">2026-04-12</terms1:created>
        <terms1:creator xml:lang="en">Diana Socola</terms1:creator>
        <terms1:creator xml:lang="en">Tomas Cuevas</terms1:creator>
        <terms1:license>https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-sa/4.0/</terms1:license>
        <schema:includedInDataCatalog>https://tomascp-sudo.github.io/medical-device-ontology/</schema:includedInDataCatalog>
        <vann5:preferredNamespacePrefix>mdcso</vann5:preferredNamespacePrefix>
        <terms2:abstract>The Medical Devices Classification and Safety Ontology provides a framework for modeling key concepts, entities, and relationships within the domain of medical devices.
It captures knowledge about device types, regulatory classes, manufacturers, and corrective actions.
Using OWL and SWRL, the ontology supports intelligent reasoning over safety-related data and facilitates interoperability, analysis, and querying within medical device information systems.</terms2:abstract>
        <terms2:created rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#date">2026-04-27</terms2:created>
        <terms2:license>https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-sa/4.0/</terms2:license>
        <vann3:preferredNamespacePrefix>mdcso</vann3:preferredNamespacePrefix>
        <rdfs:comment>This ontology is about medical devices, their classification, and the safety mechanisms associated with their use, including incidents and corrective actions.</rdfs:comment>
        <rdfs:comment xml:lang="en">This ontology provides a formal and unified representation of the European catalogue of high-risk medical devices and in vitro diagnostic devices under the MDR and IVDR regulations.</rdfs:comment>
        <rdfs:isDefinedBy>The authors of this ontology have been:

Diana Alejandrina Socola

Tomás Cuevas</rdfs:isDefinedBy>
        <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">Ontology for High-Risk Medical Devices and IVDs</rdfs:label>
        <owl:versionInfo>This is V1.0</owl:versionInfo>
        <owl:versionInfo>Version 1.0</owl:versionInfo>
    </owl:Ontology>
    


